race.comment: DOUBLET (5) is knocking on the door, placing in his past three. He stepped up to 1950m last start at Yarra Valley and just found one better as favourite. Like him going to 2050m now and he should be very hard to hold out. RAPIDO RIVER (10) drops back in trip off a short break of 11 weeks having been close up in third over 2435m at Mornington when last seen. The run over this trip at Cranbourne prior reads well for this. MOLESWORTH (6) finished fourth on debut two runs back then again just missed the placings last start start over 1700m at Warrnambool, beaten 4.5 lengths. Open to improvement and can win. SOUL MISTRESS (13) ran well fresh at Sale and should be improved now. Hard to hold out. FEDORA (14) maps well and can give a sight.
